article.description: Tray Boyd III scored 16 points off the bench to carry East Tennessee State to an 88-63 win over Samford on Wednesday night for the Buccaneers' 11th straight home victory.
article.headline: ETSU wins 11th straight at home, beats Samford 88-63
article.linkText: ETSU wins 11th straight at home, beats Samford 88-63
article.story: JOHNSON CITY, Tenn. -- Tray Boyd III scored 16 points off the bench to carry East Tennessee State to an 88-63 win over Samford on Wednesday night for the Buccaneers' 11th straight home victory. Joe Hugley had 14 points for East Tennessee State (16-3, 5-1 Southern Conference). Lucas N'Guessan added 12 points and Daivien Williamson had 11. Josh Sharkey had 18 points and three assists for the Bulldogs (8-11, 2-3), but committed seven turnovers. Robert Allen added 12 points. Jalen Dupree had seven rebounds. East Tennessee State matches up against Western Carolina on the road on Saturday.
